1. "git init" -> for initializing the local repository as git repository
2. Add the files in your new local repository,
your files now be staged for the first commit
"git add . "
3. "git status" -> it will show all the files 
which you have staged for the commit
4. commit the files that you have staged in your local repository 
"git commit -m "first commit" "
5. copy the remote url 
6. git remote add origin //paste_the_url_here
7. pushing the code from the local repository to github 
"git push -u origin master"
---username -> enter your github username
---password -> enter your github password.
